newsitem.title: FRANCE: MATIF February wheat expires without delivery.
newsitem.headline: MATIF February wheat expires without delivery.

text.p: MATIF February wheat, the third month of the futures contract, expired without delivery, the French exchange said on Thursday.
February open interest after Wednesday's last trading day was zero, a MATIF spokeswoman said.
A final 22 lots of February wheat changed hands on Wednesday, she said.
MATIF launched the contract on July 5 with an inaugural volume of 153 lots but slack physical markets have limited trade.
MATIF has said the contract needed time to develop as legal problems delayed its launch by several months.
It has avoided giving a volume target for the contract but sources close to the exchange have said 1,000 lots daily would have been considered a success.
Since the launch, open interest peaked on December 20 at 1,092 lots while daily volume hit a record high of 320 lots on September 26.
December volume reached 774 lots, with an average 37 lots traded daily, the latest MATIF statistics show.
